uccess rate with projects located throughout the country. This success rate is derived from his expertise in offering cost effective project solutions as well as his ability to solicit and work with qualified subcontractors. Kenny began working in the construction industry in 1990 as a Quantity Surveyor and has since held the roles of Estimator, Project Manager, Chief Estimator, Vice President and Owner of various companies.\n \nKenny graduated from Kansas State University with a bachelor’s degree in Construction Science & Management.','Kenny Hoy','','publish','open','open','','kenny-hoy','','','2015-03-21 20:57:36','2015-03-21 20:57:36','',0,'http://dev.unitedexcel.com/?post_type=people&amp;p=52',0,'people','',0),(188,1,'2015-03-21 21:29:15','2015-03-21 21:29:15','Becky serves as Vice President of I-DBO Resources.  In this role, she manages the Business Development, Public Relations and Marketing functions. She also provides support on proposal preparation.\r\n  \r\nBecky’s career in the construction industry began 12 years ago when she began working within the marketing department for a general contractor in Wichita, Kansas. Since joining the I-DBO Resources family of companies, she has worked as a Project Administrator, Marketing Coordinator and Marketing Director prior to her current role of Vice President. Becky’s career experience has provided her with valuable insight into the entire construction process, beginning at the receipt of the request for proposal all the way until project completion.\r\n \r\nShe is well-versed in working with estimators and pre-construction managers during the proposal stage, as well as coordinating with owners, architects, engineers and all other members of the project team.\r\n\r\nBecky graduated from Kansas State University with a bachelor’s degree in Public Relations.','Becky Cullinan','','publish','open','open','','becky-cullinan','','','2015-03-24 20:12:21','2015-03-24 20:12:21','',0,'http://ue.2020creative.org/?post_type=peo