rvice goal. In addition, our family of communities participates in or sponsors a variety of local, regional and national charitable initiatives.\r\n\r\nRecent initiatives have benefitted Harvesters food bank, the Joshua Chamberlain Society, Hope House, Coat-A-Kid, SSM Cardinal Glennon Children’s Medical Center, Urban Peak, the Boys and Girls Club of Weld County, the Cystic Fibrosis Foundation, St. Mary’s Breast Center, SIDS Resources, Inc. and more.\r\n\r\nIn this way, we are giving back to the communities we live, work and play in.','Community Involvement','','publish','open','open','','community-involvement','','','2015-04-17 20:30:18','2015-04-17 20:30:18','',0,'http://ue.2020creative.org/?page_id=253',0,'page','',0),(255,1,'2015-03-24 17:25:03','2015-03-24 17:25:03',' ','','','publish','open','open','','255','','','2015-04-28 14:11:55','2015-04-28 14:11:55','',0,'http://ue.2020creative.org/?p=255',5,'nav_menu_item','',0),(256,1,'2015-03-24 18:17:09','2015-03-24 18:17:09','','Our Expertise','','publish','open','open','','what-we-do','','','2015-04-28 14:11:55','2015-04-28 14:11:55','',0,'http://ue.2020creative.org/?p=256',6,'nav_menu_item','',0),(257,1,'2015-03-24 18:19:17','2015-03-24 18:19:17','With a dedicated focus on being the highest quality healthcare design/builder in the industry, our family of companies is highly experienced in designing, managing, constructing and outfitting medical facilities. Since 1994, we have completed nearly 1,000 healthcare renovation, repair, addition and new construction projects.\r\n\r\nUEC, UED and Mill Creek employ a full staff of REVIT trained architects, engineers (including electrical, mechanical and structural), project managers and project engineers, estimators, transition planners, initial outfitters and designers (including electrical, interior, plumbing and mechanical) who continually stay apprised of cutting-edge health care industry and technical developments, including sustainability and safety.\r\n\r\nOur portfo