neers (including electrical, mechanical, structural and project), project managers and project engineers, estimators, transition planners, initial outfitters and designers (including electrical, interior, plumbing and mechanical) who continually stay apprised of cutting-edge health care industry and technical developments, including sustainability and safety.\n\nOur portfolio of experience includes hospitals, ambulatory care facilities, research facilities, medical office buildings and senior living facilities as well as the installation and relocation of complex equipment, including MRIs, CTs, brain labs, hybrid ORs and LASIK laser equipment.  Many of these projects occurred in fully operational facilities, requiring excellent transition support to minimize operational disruption.\n\nWith a proven track record of providing timely deliverables within budget and per scope, we can meet virtually any health care design need.\n','Healthcare Expertise','','inherit','open','open','','257-autosave-v1','','','2015-04-17 19:05:12','2015-04-17 19:05:12','',257,'http://ue.2020creative.org/257-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(299,1,'2015-03-24 21:51:42','2015-03-24 21:51:42','<h2>Deliver profitable, quality, complex projects on schedule, on budget with complete customer satisfaction through caring, committed employees.</h2>\r\n[tt_rule]','Mission','','publish','open','open','','mission','','','2015-04-27 16:57:11','2015-04-27 16:57:11','',0,'http://ue.2020creative.org/?page_id=299',0,'page','',0),(304,1,'2015-03-24 22:16:59','2015-03-24 22:16:59','We believe integrating the design-build-outfitting processes is the future of health care design, as it allows these services to be provided more efficiently and effectively than traditional design/build segmented disciplines. Involving key multidisciplinary participants through all phases of construction, from bid through closeout, positions all parties to proactively address potential changes, scope issues or risks.\r\n\r\nThis collaboration and enhanced communication minimizes uncertainties in design interpretation, provides a better defined, more proactive set of project objectives and eases problem resolution. It also establishes a more accurate budget and schedule.\r\n\r\nEveryone is working towards the same goal with the same agenda, so risk is reduced. Costly man hours are not wasted in reconciling project segments or providing rework in the field.\r\n\r\nIn addition to enhanced quality, the efficiencies recognized through integration of operations also means quicker project delivery and cost savings to the Owner.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://ue.2020creative.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Cool_Infographic_A.gif\" alt=\"Cool_Infographic_A\" width=\"\" height=\"\" class=\"img-responsive\" />','Integrated Design-Built-Outfitting Advantage','','publish','open','open','','integrated-design-built-outfitting-advantage','','','2015-04-01 16:34:42','2015-04-01 16:34:42','',53,'http://ue.2020creative.org/?page_id=304',0,'page','',0),(306,1,'2015-03-24 22:17:35','2015-03-24 22:17:35',' ','','','publish','open','open','','306','','','2015-04-28 14:11:55','2015-04-28 14:11:55','',53,'http://ue.2020creative.org/?p=306',7,'nav_menu_item','',0),(308,1,'2015-03-24 22:26:35','2015-03-24 22:26:35','Mill Creek (MC) is a woman-owned small business that specializes in the outfitting of furniture, fixtures &amp; equipment (FF&amp;E), equipment planning, and transition/move management for commercial and healthcare facilities. The team offers project management solutions for budgeting, scheduling, procurement &amp; installation and helps execute even the most complex transitions with minimal downtime.','Mill Creek','','publish','open','open','','mill-creek','','','2015-04-24 17:30:12','2015-04-24 17:30:12','',0,'http://ue.2020creative.org/?p=308',0,'post','',0),(310,1,'2015-03-24 22:27:12','2015-03-24 22:27:12','United Excel Design (UED) provides a complete package of architectural design and engineering services. 